1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,740
We had a great time. I live to tell about it. Praise God.

2
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:08,640
And I got more points than last year. I still lost, but at least I scored.

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:11,420
So, I mean, that was good. Yay.

4
00:00:11,780 --> 00:00:17,200
And I want to thank Mario and the team for putting on a phenomenal second annual tournament.

5
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:18,760
That was awesome.

6
00:00:19,380 --> 00:00:25,480
And I want to thank Paul Delgado as well.

7
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:28,580
Paul was kind of our emcee, master of ceremonies for the event.

8
00:00:28,580 --> 00:00:32,840
He shared a nice, quick gospel message at the very beginning and prayed for the event

9
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:35,720
and just did a great job of kind of making everybody feel welcome

10
00:00:35,720 --> 00:00:38,560
and cared for and encouraged.

11
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:41,000
So thank you, Paul, for your hard work there.

12
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:41,480
Thank you.

13
00:00:45,350 --> 00:00:47,410
And again, if you are new to our church family,

14
00:00:47,490 --> 00:00:50,990
we have a wonderful karate ministry that has now got its own tournament

15
00:00:50,990 --> 00:00:53,190
and may go international someday.

16
00:00:53,350 --> 00:00:56,690
We send actually karate students around the world sometimes,

17
00:00:56,830 --> 00:00:59,810
and they come back with buckets of trophies and medals,

18
00:00:59,890 --> 00:01:00,750
and we're proud of them.

19
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:03,770
And if you want to be a part of this thing, it's free.

20
00:01:04,550 --> 00:01:04,890
Okay?

21
00:01:05,330 --> 00:01:08,670
You can't get free karate anywhere in this community.

22
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:13,630
Tuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays, beginning class is at 6.30.

23
00:01:13,990 --> 00:01:16,550
The advanced class and team is at 7.30.

24
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:18,150
You just come on out.

25
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:20,070
I don't care if you have a little white outfit or not.

26
00:01:20,130 --> 00:01:21,290
We'll get you all that stuff.

27
00:01:21,670 --> 00:01:24,710
If you want to work out, though, and just tone up, come on out.

28
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:25,990
You'll have a great time.

29
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:28,770
And then you get to take on your pastor someday.

30
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:30,790
So you can do that.

31
00:01:31,270 --> 00:01:31,870
It was great.

32
00:01:31,970 --> 00:01:33,250
Thank you all for being a part of that.

33
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:45,510
Well, listen, let's start off here, and John, professional golfer, we go from karate to golf, both things I like, also not good at, but like it, and this gentleman, Paul Azinger, how many know who he is?

34
00:01:46,010 --> 00:01:53,490
Ever heard of him? A few golfer fans out there? Okay, well, this guy was diagnosed with cancer at 33 years old. That'll rock your world, wouldn't it?

35
00:01:55,440 --> 00:02:00,600
He had just won a PGA championship, had 10 tournament victories to his credit,

36
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:03,040
and he wrote this about that experience.

37
00:02:03,140 --> 00:02:07,320
He said, a genuine feeling of fear came over me.

38
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,520
He wrote, I could die from cancer.

39
00:02:11,660 --> 00:02:14,340
And then another reality hit me even harder.

40
00:02:15,020 --> 00:02:20,720
I'm going to die eventually anyway, whether from cancer or for something else.

41
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,980
It's just a question of when.

42
00:02:25,730 --> 00:02:26,770
Well, that freaked him out.

43
00:02:27,010 --> 00:02:31,950
And he said, everything I had accomplished in golf suddenly became meaningless.

44
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:35,490
All I wanted to do, he says, was live.

45
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:43,100
And then he remembered something that Larry Moody, who teaches the Bible study on the tour, had said this.

46
00:02:43,140 --> 00:02:47,920
He said, Zinger, we're not in the land of the living going to the land of the dying.

47
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:54,020
He said, we're in the land of the dying trying to get to the land of the living.

48
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:57,800
And that really changed his worldview.

49
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:05,040
Well, this guy, Paul Azinger, he recovered from the cancer through chemotherapy, returned to the tour.

50
00:03:05,970 --> 00:03:10,170
He did well, but that bout with cancer changed his life.

51
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:11,860
And he wrote this.

52
00:03:12,650 --> 00:03:16,790
I've made a lot of money since I've been on the tour, and I've won a lot of tournaments,

53
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:19,230
but that happiness is always temporary.

54
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:27,970
The only way you will ever have true contentment is a personal, personal relationship with Jesus Christ.

55
00:03:28,630 --> 00:03:32,170
I'm not saying that nothing ever bothers me and I don't have problems,

56
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:36,990
but I feel like I found the answer to the six-foot hole.

57
00:03:40,940 --> 00:03:45,680
There's a man who had it all, but then he realized he didn't have it all.

58
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:47,680
He had no peace.

59
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:52,990
He had no ultimate purpose until he met Jesus.

60
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:58,260
And once he really met Jesus and followed Jesus,

61
00:03:58,260 --> 00:04:02,340
it changed his life and his outlook and his perspective

62
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:05,760
and his whole world was radically changed.

63
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:10,650
In our second installment in this study in the book of John, we're going to look at Jesus'

64
00:04:10,910 --> 00:04:14,050
dialogue with somebody else who really had it all

65
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:18,940
or so he thought. I want you to turn with me in your Bibles if you've got them or take a look

66
00:04:18,940 --> 00:04:23,170
at the screen to John chapter 3 starting in verse 1.

67
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:25,920
It goes like this.

68
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:35,470
leader named Nicodemus, a Pharisee, came to speak with

69
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:39,510
Jesus. Teacher, he said, we all know that God has sent you

70
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:43,610
to teach us. Your miraculous signs are proof enough that God

71
00:04:43,610 --> 00:04:48,010
is with you. And Jesus replied, I assure you

72
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:51,510
unless you are born again, you can never see the kingdom of God.

73
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:56,830
What do you mean? exclaimed Nicodemus. How can an old man go back

74
00:04:56,830 --> 00:05:01,440
to his mother's womb and be born again? The truth is

75
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:05,620
no one can enter the kingdom of God without being born of water and the Spirit.

76
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:08,820
Humans can reproduce only human life,

77
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,860
but the Holy Spirit gives new life from heaven.

78
00:05:12,790 --> 00:05:16,170
So don't be surprised at my statement that you must be born again,

79
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:20,250
just as you can hear the wind but can't tell where it comes from or where it's going,

80
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:23,750
so you can't explain how people are born of the Spirit.

81
00:05:24,610 --> 00:05:26,670
What do you mean, Nicodemus responded?

82
00:05:26,670 --> 00:05:32,230
You are a well-respected Jewish teacher, and you don't understand these things?

83
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:37,470
I assure you I'm telling you what we know and have seen, and yet you won't believe us.

84
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:41,970
But if you don't even believe me when I tell you about things that happen here on earth,

85
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:45,590
how can you possibly believe if I tell you what's going on in heaven?

86
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:51,140
For only I, the Son of Man, have come to earth, and will return to heaven again.

87
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:55,300
And as Moses lifted up the bronze snake on a pole in the wilderness,

88
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,120
so I, the Son of Man, must be lifted up on a pole,

89
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:02,960
so that everyone who believes in me will have eternal life.

90
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:07,780
For God so loved the world that he gave his only Son

91
00:06:07,780 --> 00:06:12,700
so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life.

92
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:17,940
God did not send his Son into the world to condemn it but to save it.

93
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:21,640
There is no judgment awaiting those who trust him,

94
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:27,460
but those who do not trust him have already been judged for not believing in the Son of God.

95
00:06:28,170 --> 00:06:30,450
Their judgment is based on this fact.

96
00:06:31,010 --> 00:06:35,670
The light from heaven came into the world, but they loved the darkness more than the light.

97
00:06:37,570 --> 00:06:39,050
Their actions were evil.

98
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:42,590
They hate the light because they want to sin in the darkness.

99
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:48,110
They stay away from the light for fear their sins will be exposed and they will be punished.

100
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:55,850
But those who do what is right come to the light gladly so everyone can see what they are doing, what God wants.

101
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,480
I want us to enter that story.

102
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:02,980
For some of you, that's a very famous story.

103
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,540
You may have heard that a lot of times.

104
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,660
For some of you, this is perhaps the first time.

105
00:07:08,910 --> 00:07:11,930
And I want us to, wherever we are in terms of interacting with it,

106
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:15,310
to come to a place where we enter this story this morning.

107
00:07:15,390 --> 00:07:17,210
I want you to feel the darkness.

108
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:22,770
I want you to smell the dark, cool air as it surrounds these characters.

109
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:28,660
And I want you to see the man approaching Jesus from out of the night.

110
00:07:28,660 --> 00:07:34,710
I want you to put yourself right to the side of Jesus and Nicodemus

111
00:07:34,710 --> 00:07:40,460
because you're going to listen in on this very insightful conversation.

112
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:49,350
Nicodemus, this religious leader, a rabbi, a teacher of the law,

113
00:07:50,700 --> 00:07:51,880
he had his act together.

114
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:54,980
He believed the right things.

115
00:07:55,910 --> 00:07:58,090
He stayed away from the wrong things.

116
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:01,040
He was a squeaky clean kind of guy.

117
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,790
No fault here.

118
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:09,650
And this religious leader, Nicodemus, comes to Jesus at night.

119
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:13,080
This is the real Nick at night.

120
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,740
Comes at night.

121
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:23,980
That was bad, I know.

122
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,180
But you were listening.

123
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:28,000
I got you here, right?

124
00:08:29,430 --> 00:08:32,370
Nicodemus, why does he come at dark?

125
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:33,810
Why does he come at night?

126
00:08:34,450 --> 00:08:36,390
Why does he come under cloak of darkness?

127
00:08:36,730 --> 00:08:38,770
Perhaps he's afraid of being seen.

128
00:08:39,570 --> 00:08:44,250
I mean, after all, Jesus has performed a miracle at a wedding.

129
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:48,380
and kind of opened up that he's got supernatural power.

130
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:52,380
He's just destroyed the temple in the chapter before.

131
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:56,350
This man, how do we say this?

132
00:08:56,450 --> 00:08:57,910
This man is subversive.

133
00:08:58,830 --> 00:09:02,670
This man, Jesus, is not safe for the religious establishment.

134
00:09:03,370 --> 00:09:05,390
And if you're going to hang out with this guy,

135
00:09:05,730 --> 00:09:09,470
you might be in trouble if you're part of the powers that be.

136
00:09:10,970 --> 00:09:14,790
I don't think Nicodemus wants to be associated with him in the daylight.

137
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:15,890
He comes at night.

138
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:22,360
And if you can just picture this scene where Jesus is on a stage, if you will,

139
00:09:22,820 --> 00:09:26,640
and it's totally dark except one cone of light coming down on Jesus.

140
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:30,260
And Nicodemus is hovering around just outside of the light.

141
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:33,140
And he comes in to talk to Jesus.

142
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:36,480
Now, theologian to theologian, they begin to talk.

143
00:09:37,290 --> 00:09:41,180
Teacher, we all know that God has sent you to teach us.

144
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:46,520
Your miraculous signs, the wedding at Cana, your disturbing the temple, your miracles,

145
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:49,020
We think these are proof that God is with you.

146
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:50,100
We will buy that.

147
00:09:51,860 --> 00:09:55,860
But see, Jesus is not interested in talking about signs.

148
00:09:57,520 --> 00:10:02,620
Jesus is interested in the hearts of men and women and their connection with God.

149
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,120
And Jesus says this.

150
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:08,560
Jesus speaks in riddles.

151
00:10:10,090 --> 00:10:14,190
Sometimes when we hear things plainly, we don't hear it, do we?

152
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:19,070
Sometimes when your friend will talk to you or your spouse or your boyfriend or girlfriend,

153
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:20,710
and they'll be sort of veiled.

154
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:25,390
They'll hold back something or speak in humor or in riddles or puns.

155
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:26,830
It perks your ears up.

156
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:29,410
It makes you draw in to, what are you saying?

157
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:37,440
Jesus says, unless you're born again, you can never see the kingdom of God.

158
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:43,020
Friends, I want to say this.

159
00:10:43,910 --> 00:10:48,610
Sometimes we've heard this gospel story so many times that we're not listening anymore.

160
00:10:49,450 --> 00:10:50,450
We don't hear it either.

161
00:10:50,930 --> 00:10:56,310
And wherever you are this morning in your spiritual journey, I want you to really hear this.

162
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:59,680
Really open your eyes and your ears.

163
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:04,550
Unless you're born again, you can never see the kingdom of God.

164
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:07,230
Well, Nicodemus is hooked.

165
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:12,220
You can almost see the furrows in his face beginning to scrunch up

166
00:11:12,220 --> 00:11:14,240
and the frown starting to drop on his face.

167
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:16,560
You can't climb back into the womb.

168
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,120
What are you saying, Jesus?

169
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:19,840
That's ridiculous.

170
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:23,130
It's wacko.

171
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:25,460
But he's hooked.

172
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:32,530
Jesus says the truth is no one can enter the kingdom of God

173
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:34,770
without being born of water and the Spirit.

174
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:37,470
What is Jesus saying?

175
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,650
What is he really saying?

176
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,500
He's speaking to a man.

177
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:46,300
Speaking to a man who knows the Hebrew Scriptures.

178
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:50,970
And Jesus is pointing back to Scriptures like this.

179
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:53,090
From Ezekiel, listen.

180
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:57,030
God says, I will sprinkle you with water

181
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:58,790
and you will be clean.

182
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:02,250
I will cleanse you from all your impurities

183
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,630
and from all your idols.

184
00:12:04,170 --> 00:12:05,650
I will give you a new heart

185
00:12:05,650 --> 00:12:07,390
and put a new spirit in you

186
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:10,520
and I will remove your heart of stone

187
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,680
and give you a heart of flesh

188
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:15,540
and I will put my spirit in you

189
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:17,420
and move you to follow my decrees

190
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:19,760
and be careful to keep my laws.

191
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:25,980
Jesus is saying that a new age has dawned,

192
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:28,510
that God is doing a new thing.

193
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:31,460
God is working through John the Baptist

194
00:12:31,460 --> 00:12:34,760
and Jesus is now baptizing in the Spirit.

195
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:37,840
The Spirit of God is now moving with humanity.

196
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:46,100
And God's Spirit is changing people now from the inside out, from the inside out.

197
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:52,400
To be close to God is to have God's Spirit dwell within you and transform you into a new person.

198
00:12:52,780 --> 00:13:02,360
The Bible says a new creation, a new creature, that new person that delights to do what God is all about

199
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:05,420
and to be about God's business.

200
00:13:07,590 --> 00:13:10,930
But all of that is lost on Nicodemus.

201
00:13:10,930 --> 00:13:14,310
He's a rabbi. He's a teacher.

202
00:13:15,670 --> 00:13:18,010
He's supposed to know the mysteries of God.

203
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:22,860
And as he's standing there in the darkness talking to Jesus, who is the light,

204
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:27,780
he doesn't get it. He's not able to see it.

205
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:29,740
And so Jesus says,

206
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:35,160
For God so loved the world that he gave his only Son,

207
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:40,180
so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life.

208
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:44,630
God did not send his Son into the world to condemn it,

209
00:13:44,630 --> 00:13:52,370
But to save it, that, friends, is the whole story in that sentence.

210
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:59,310
That's the whole story of this whole book summed up in those sentences.

211
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:02,910
It's the whole church.

212
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:04,330
It's the whole story.

213
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:12,350
It's known as the good news that God gave his son that no one should perish but should have eternal life.

214
00:14:13,570 --> 00:14:18,400
The good news is this, that God loves you more than you can ever believe or know.

215
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,580
And that he sent his own son Jesus, not to condemn you,

216
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:27,700
but to deliver you from your own selfishness and your own soul sickness,

217
00:14:28,930 --> 00:14:33,160
that you might be in relationship with God now and forever.

218
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:36,230
That's the good news.

219
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:37,600
That's it.

220
00:14:39,330 --> 00:14:42,890
It's the greatest news you'll ever hear, that God loves you and wants to be with you forever

221
00:14:42,890 --> 00:14:46,930
and wants to impact your life and be in your life now and forever.

222
00:14:49,620 --> 00:14:54,380
When you really hear that, when you really hear that message, it cuts to your heart.

223
00:14:54,740 --> 00:14:56,240
Friends, are you listening today?

224
00:14:57,210 --> 00:14:58,190
Are you really listening?

225
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,920
Are you too settled in your beliefs and your religion to really hear this again?

226
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:05,540
I want you to hear this.

227
00:15:07,540 --> 00:15:09,040
I want you to hear it from a different translation.

228
00:15:11,060 --> 00:15:13,340
This is how much God loved the world.

229
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:18,920
He gave His Son, His one and only Son.

230
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:23,400
And this is why, so that no one need be destroyed.

231
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:28,420
By believing in him, anyone can have a whole and lasting life.

232
00:15:29,790 --> 00:15:33,890
God didn't go to all the trouble of sending his son merely to point an accusing finger,

233
00:15:34,370 --> 00:15:36,250
telling the world how bad it was.

234
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,220
He came to help.

235
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:41,500
He came to put the world right again.

236
00:15:44,580 --> 00:15:49,660
Nicodemus heard the words of Jesus, but he didn't really listen.

237
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:53,840
Nicodemus had all the head knowledge about God.

238
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:55,760
He knew the scriptures.

239
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,720
He knew the mechanics of the religion.

240
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,800
He could do it in his sleep.

241
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,200
But that's what he was towards God.

242
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:04,600
He was still asleep.

243
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:12,160
You see, you can know an awful lot about God and still miss the heart of God.

244
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:21,520
For many, the greatest distance you're ever going to travel is the 18 inches between your head and your heart.

245
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:26,040
That's a long journey for many people.

246
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:28,880
That's been a long journey for me at times.

247
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:36,420
You can know an awful lot, but if it doesn't get down to your heart, it doesn't become real.

248
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,880
You don't step out on only what you know in your head.

249
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:41,900
You step out what you know in your heart.

250
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:47,300
In biblical language, the heart is the seat of the passions and the volition and the stepping out.

251
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:50,140
And the following Jesus comes from the heart, not just the head.

252
00:16:52,370 --> 00:16:59,760
Nicodemus heard it in his head, but his life was not penetrated by Jesus Christ.

253
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:03,140
We see Nicodemus asking questions.

254
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:09,660
We'll see him later in John in various places trying to step out, but he doesn't really do it.

255
00:17:10,820 --> 00:17:15,660
And like an actor on the stage, the light fades on Nicodemus.

256
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,520
He doesn't go all the way.

257
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:28,460
You see, a disciple is a person that confesses Jesus' identity as the Son of God.

258
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:33,260
A disciple is a person who remains faithful in the journey with Jesus.

259
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:39,500
A disciple tells others about Jesus, and we don't see any of that in Nicodemus.

260
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:42,880
How about you?

261
00:17:45,620 --> 00:17:52,780
Do you have the knowledge about Jesus, but you've not yet really believed in your heart

262
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:55,710
and stepped out to follow him?

263
00:17:58,330 --> 00:18:00,650
Do you confess him as your leader and forgiven?

264
00:18:01,090 --> 00:18:02,450
Do you stick close by him?

265
00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:03,950
Do you tell others about him?

266
00:18:04,470 --> 00:18:06,230
Those are the traits of a disciple.

267
00:18:06,530 --> 00:18:07,230
Is that you?

268
00:18:07,230 --> 00:18:11,740
or are you just going through the motions?

269
00:18:15,390 --> 00:18:17,090
What Jesus is getting at is this.

270
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:20,050
That humanity is broken down beyond all repair.

271
00:18:20,690 --> 00:18:22,970
God is not interested in merely fixing us.

272
00:18:23,030 --> 00:18:27,270
He's interested in rebuilding us from the inside out.

273
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:31,110
It's not about shaving off rough edges

274
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:34,170
and just kind of trying to tweak you a little bit.

275
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:39,110
This is major reconstructive surgery from the inside out.

276
00:18:39,930 --> 00:18:41,810
Make you a new creature, a new creation.

277
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:45,280
The old has passed, the new has come, says Paul.

278
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:51,450
True religion, friends, is not just about ethical behavior.

279
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:53,380
That's a part of it.

280
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:58,740
But it's not just about doing the right things or having the right knowledge.

281
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:04,180
I'm concerned that in the church we've talked a lot about knowing your Bibles.

282
00:19:07,020 --> 00:19:11,510
You have to be and live the truth of the Scriptures.

283
00:19:12,070 --> 00:19:17,510
And that comes from grabbing onto Jesus and having Him transform your life

284
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:19,030
and to really go with Him.

285
00:19:19,430 --> 00:19:21,890
Then the head knowledge becomes heart knowledge.

286
00:19:23,940 --> 00:19:28,140
True religion is not about following a code of rules precisely.

287
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:31,520
That's a trap.

288
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:38,040
Jesus is saying to us that true religion is not about finding God within you

289
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:43,990
and fanning it into flame and becoming divine, because we're not.

290
00:19:45,290 --> 00:19:46,650
If you get honest, you know we're not.

291
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:51,420
The only way that God comes into you is when you invite him through his Holy Spirit

292
00:19:51,420 --> 00:19:52,260
to take up residence.

293
00:19:52,380 --> 00:19:53,040
You are not God.

294
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:55,360
You invite him, though, to dwell in you.

295
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,560
That's the Christian story.

296
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:05,690
True religion is not just something on the vertical or rather on the horizontal plane.

297
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:06,770
It's vertical.

298
00:20:06,930 --> 00:20:07,750
It starts there.

299
00:20:08,850 --> 00:20:12,150
It starts by being born from above.

300
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,600
It's not something that we do.

301
00:20:18,030 --> 00:20:21,150
It's something you open yourself up to as God does in you.

302
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:24,650
Will you open yourself up to let God do it in you?

303
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,620
Will you say, yes, I'll follow.

304
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:32,760
Now begin to do your work in me and I'll follow you in that work that you're doing.

305
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:37,860
The Bible says, I'm going to remove the heart of stone

306
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:40,710
and give you a heart of flesh.

307
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,160
That's what it's about.

308
00:20:44,870 --> 00:20:46,050
I'm going to summarize it this way.

309
00:20:48,170 --> 00:20:49,750
Jesus is saying these things.

310
00:20:50,630 --> 00:20:52,690
Number one, all people live in darkness.

311
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,780
When we get brutally honest with ourselves,

312
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:58,660
we realize that we live in darkness and we like darkness.

313
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:07,410
But when you get tired of going your own way

314
00:21:07,410 --> 00:21:12,400
and living with the consequences of the destructive behaviors in our lives

315
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:15,420
and our selfishness and our inward focus

316
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:18,220
and our obsession on all the wrong things

317
00:21:18,220 --> 00:21:20,200
and our addictions and our habits

318
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,900
and all the things that bring us down

319
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,500
and drag us into the pit.

320
00:21:23,580 --> 00:21:24,760
When you're tired of those things

321
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:26,540
and you say, I want a new start,

322
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:28,440
Jesus promises a new start.

323
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:31,860
And believers, number two,

324
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:34,260
are willing to open their lives to God's scrutiny,

325
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:36,480
are open to coming into the light,

326
00:21:38,390 --> 00:21:38,910
which is Jesus.

327
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:46,140
And then we believe what Jesus did for us on the cross

328
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:50,960
Let's take all of our sinfulness and nail it away.

329
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:57,660
And after you come to light, we can live a new life

330
00:21:57,660 --> 00:22:00,200
and be empowered by the Holy Spirit

331
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:05,200
and live a life of gratitude that comes from God saving us.

332
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:12,400
But you know my concern is there's millions of religious people

333
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:17,380
that sit in church week after week going through the motions

334
00:22:17,380 --> 00:22:20,510
and they've got the knowledge and the rituals

335
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:22,570
and they've missed the relationship.

336
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:28,320
And it can happen here, it can happen in every church, in the community, and around the world.

337
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:30,060
We go through the motions.

338
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:33,500
We don't have the relationship.

339
00:22:37,190 --> 00:22:39,930
And so I just want to ask, Fullerton, are you ready to step into the light?

340
00:22:41,590 --> 00:22:46,490
And if you have not really stepped into the light and allowed God's Spirit to take up residence and to dwell

341
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:52,520
and to really have His way in your life, I'm going to give you a chance to do that today.

342
00:22:55,260 --> 00:23:00,630
And some of you are sitting back and you are dying a thousand deaths because you know this is true.

343
00:23:00,630 --> 00:23:03,450
and it's not my words, the Holy Spirit

344
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:04,550
beginning to talk to you

345
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:07,600
and you're thinking, what are they going to say?

346
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:08,860
I've been here for years.

347
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,240
I'm supposed to know it all.

348
00:23:12,660 --> 00:23:13,280
It doesn't matter.

349
00:23:15,230 --> 00:23:17,250
If you need to get some things right with the Lord

350
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:19,990
as we give this service to conclusion,

351
00:23:20,450 --> 00:23:22,310
I'm going to invite you in a few minutes to come

352
00:23:22,310 --> 00:23:24,450
and to get some things settled with the Lord

353
00:23:24,450 --> 00:23:29,170
because 2003 is a year that we don't know

354
00:23:29,170 --> 00:23:29,870
what's going to happen.

355
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:32,540
We don't know from day to day

356
00:23:32,540 --> 00:23:33,540
if we're going to be here tomorrow

357
00:23:35,730 --> 00:23:39,050
And I'm not here to scare you and to say that, you know, nukes are going to come from Korea.

358
00:23:39,170 --> 00:23:40,490
I don't know what's going to happen.

359
00:23:41,340 --> 00:23:42,820
But friends, these are dangerous times.

360
00:23:44,710 --> 00:23:46,310
And it's not a time to play religion.

361
00:23:47,930 --> 00:23:51,130
It is not a time to impress people by faking it.

362
00:23:51,860 --> 00:23:53,000
It's time to get real.

363
00:23:54,930 --> 00:24:00,370
And if you're not being real with God, don't leave today without getting real with Him.

364
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:03,290
And I'm not going to judge you.

365
00:24:03,310 --> 00:24:04,030
We're not going to judge you.

366
00:24:04,030 --> 00:24:05,310
We're just going to love you and pray for you.

367
00:24:07,090 --> 00:24:08,290
Are you ready to step into the light?

368
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:13,000
Are you ready to put aside religion and have a relationship with the God who loves you?

369
00:24:15,070 --> 00:24:22,630
Are you ready to be born from above or known as born again by God's Spirit?

370
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:30,220
As you're thinking and praying and dealing with God, I want you to hear the words to this song.

371
00:24:31,550 --> 00:24:32,610
And then we'll talk again in a minute.

